{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we suddenly had an influx of kids that the rest of the kids immediately called the Cubans, because they came from Cuba.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were all German kids, but we called them-- they were sort of a separate group and we called them the Cubans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that name stuck.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the way, the people who disembarked from the same ship, who disembarked in England-- and those children were also sent to organizations, to a home-- we found out later that the English kids-- not the English kids, but the German kids who were-- Austrian kids who were there before-- termed them the Cubans, also.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So then, both in France and in Austria, we had this called the Cuban population, or the Cuban kids.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were all German and Austrian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the kids were-- the oldest was 15.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The youngest that came was about 5 or 6.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So-- but-- number of people-- the number of kids kept increasing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And other things that were happening is that the parents would get out and pick up the children and leave, so it made room for more kids.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So there was a constantly changing population.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Sundays was always a visitor day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I remember feeling very, very lonely, because I never got any visitors.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I felt it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, there were times when I wanted to cry, because other kids got visitors and I didn't.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were a lot of other kids that didn't get visitors, but, you know, we all felt the same thing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was correspondence with my parents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We wrote letters.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I have-- I have copies of many of the letters that my parents sent me-- which I gave the originals to the Weisenthal Center, here.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They have the originals of all my documents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So there was correspondence.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
